# Normalize line endings so vendored scripts/notes don't churn across OSes.
* text=auto eol=lf

# --- Conflict-free merges for append-only / generated files ---
# `merge=union` resolves a conflict by KEEPING BOTH SIDES instead of leaving
# <<<<<<< markers. This is what spares non-technical Obsidian users from seeing
# conflicts during Obsidian Git's LOCAL pull/merge (where they actually hit them).
#
# Caveat: GitHub's server-side merge IGNORES custom merge drivers, so a PR that
# touches these files may still conflict in the GitHub UI. That's fine here —
# content (log.md) flows straight to `main` via auto-sync, not through PRs.
log.md merge=union
# INDEX.md is regenerated by sync-skills.sh; union avoids spurious conflicts
.agents/skills/INDEX.md merge=union

# --- Binary assets: never try to diff or merge ---
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf  binary
*.excalidraw binary
